parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty tire sensor can cause the tire warning indicator to illuminate, leading to false alarms and potentially distracting the driver. In some cases, the sensor failure may not detect actual tire pressure issues, which can lead to tire failure, accidents, or loss of control.
symptoms: The tire warning indicator is illuminated
the tire sensor needs to be replaced

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dry Rotting of Michelin LTX M/S Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dry rotting of tires can cause cracks, leading to tire failure, accidents, or loss of control. This can occur even when the tires appear to be in good condition, making it a potential safety hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect for Recall Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can lead to delays in fixing safety-critical issues, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: local dealer does not have necessary equipment
manufacturer exceeds reasonable time for recall repair.
